. If you’re #1 at the top of leaderboard when the contest ends… WOO-HOOO! You will be contacted via email by a Celebrities Squared Inc. representative. You will then communicate via email and phone so we can gather the necessary information to get you your prize. You will need to sign an affidavit of eligibility, liability and, where legal, a publicity release and send it back to us within seven days of notification. We can also add, before you start play, other qualifications we want, such as a background check. Once this is done we confirm you as the winner. If you don’t get back to us, don’t sign one of the required forms, are unable to claim a Prize, don’t meet qualifications or pose a threat to Celebrities Squared, the Celebrity or Prize provider, you will not win and will not receive a prize or any substitution. We will in this instance disqualify that person and proceed to contact the second highest scorer of a Contest to award the Contest prize. Travel companions are also required to sign a liability/publicity release prior to issuance of a prize that allows a friend to accompany a prize winner. WHAT ARE THE RESTRICTIONS OR CONDITIONS ON A PRIZE? We describe each prize within the Contest, including the approximate retail value for that prize. Refer to the terms and conditions for more details we would like you to read. Some prizes have extra restrictions or conditions. We post these in the specific rules for that Contest. For all travel prizes, unless otherwise specified, you must travel on the dates allowed, all airfare is coach class and hotel accommodations are standard class. Any meetings with Celebrities are subject to security and background checks. For international travel, you are responsible to obtain all necessary travel authorizations, visas, or other documentation. All other expenses are your responsibility. Travel restrictions, conditions and limitations may apply. The prize value may vary depending on point of departure, travel dates and fare/rate fluctuations. And because stuff happens, we can’t be responsible for any cancellations, delays, diversions or substitutions, or any act or omission of any third person or acts of nature with respect to the trip. Lost or stolen tickets, travel vouchers or certificates or similar items once they are in your possession, will not be replaced. Winner and guest must travel on same itinerary. If you or your guest are, in our opinion, obnoxious, threatening, abusive, or harassing we can terminate the trip or prize, in whole or in part, and send you both home with no further compensation. Your guest must be of legal age of majority in his/her jurisdiction of residence, or your child or legal ward (unless otherwise approved by us). If you live within a one hundred (100) mile radius of the site where the prize is to be performed, we may provide ground transportation instead. We spend a lot of time thinking up the most amazing prizes possible, so prizes can’t be transferred or substituted, except that we can substitute a prize of equal or greater value. And you might not love taxes, but income taxes on the value of your prize are your responsibility and you have to pay them. We’ll give you an IRS W9 form. WINNER PROMOTION By accepting the prize, you agree that we can use your name, residential city, state and country, photograph, voice and/or other likeness and prize information to tell everyone how awesome the prize was. This means we can include you in advertising and trade and promotional materials for Celebrities Squared Inc., in any form of media (including media that’s not yet known), and that we can do so without any additional compensation. This only applies unless otherwise prohibited by law. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION. We want to get to know you! And so do our Celebrities and Prize providers. So when you enter a sweepstakes, we’ll collect some information about you. Check out our privacy policy at www.CelebritiesSquared.com to see what we collect and how we use i